history.content:
Are you a freshman or junior transfer in engineering or intended CS and would like guidance in surviving Cal? Take Engineering 98: An Insider’s Guide to Berkeley Engineering!

We are a 1 unit Pass/No Pass student-run DeCal designed and taught by Berkeley engineering upperclassmen. Class meets one hour a week, where our instructors will cover topics such as professional development, extracurricular involvement, campus resources, and many others--basically giving you a head start in everything you will do in the next few years at Cal. We also have 11 different sections at different days, times, and locations - you will definitely find a section that works for your schedule!

For more information including enrollment, visit our website at http://e98.berkeley.edu and our DeCal page at https://decal.berkeley.edu/courses/4526! For any questions, email us at e98coords@gmail.com.
